Very cool spot to hang, nostalgic old school games and vibe. Funny notes on the bathroom wall by owners on what to do if sick or feeling sick. Good specials and happy hours. Outdoor space in the back. Good music but the drinks aren't too great. There's one guy who is always there making the drinks and they never come out good to me. We tried going another night to see if they had anybody else behind the bar but it's always the same guy. So I try to keep it basic so it can be drinkable. But maybe by now they have hired other bar staff. I would definitely recommend the spot to hang out or to meet up with friends but keep it simple when it comes to drinks like beer or vodka and cranberry. Everything else about the spot is pretty cool and the bbq pizzas are delicious btw!! :)  To the owner--- I don't recall the issue or what I ordered (most likely a margarita as that's my favorite drink). I think they were mostly made improperly like too much triple sec or lime juice. I tried different drinks but none of them tasted good. The guy always bartending was the young black guy. Can't recall his name though. Thanks for offering the free drink I appreciate it :-D
